
Unsupervised Learning and Clustering Approaches

Unsupervised Learnning 
- discovering structure in the data without labels 
- labels are 'categories' of the data 
    - example would be whether the patient died 
    - yes or no 
    - multiclass categories
- need to measure 'similarity' between data points in order to separate data into different bins 
- similarity in terms of distance using 'K MEANS' --> super simple

Lloyd's Algorithm 
- Specify a number of buckets and partition points into buckets so that each point in the bucket was strongly represented by the mean 
- Dataset with n vectors, each vector is m long 
    - age, income level, etc. for 100 people 
- Partition into K distinc group by minimizing cluster sum of squared distance
    - calculate mean of all points and want points of bucket to be similar to the mean
- Measure similarity with eucladian distance d(x,y)^2= ||x-y||^2
- Need to know the number of clusters 

Manhattan norm (p=1) --> distance as sum of absolute differences
Euclidean norm (p=2) --> straight line distance, for K-means 
Maximum norm (p=inf) --> distanceas the largest component difference 


